    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vases designed for or used to hold offerings of food, libations, or flowers at a grave or tomb. Examples include those from ancient Egypt, Greece, Rome, and China, where they were often designed in pairs. They remain common as flower receptacles in modern cemeteries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
